'cause it's a shite tune
anyways,

23:26.709 --> 23:28.058
I wouldn't bother with it.

23:43.378 --> 23:44.205
[EXHALES SHAKILY]

23:59.438 --> 24:00.917
I was too harsh yesterday.

24:01.091 --> 24:03.311
Yesterday, he says.

24:03.485 --> 24:05.748
I know well
you was too harsh yesterday.

24:05.922 --> 24:06.619
And today.

24:08.142 --> 24:08.838
I just, uh...

24:11.537 --> 24:15.192
I just have this tremendous
sense of time slippin' away
on me, Padraic.

24:15.366 --> 24:17.238
And I think I need to spend
the time I have left

24:17.412 --> 24:19.414
thinking and composing.

24:21.372 --> 24:23.418
Just trying not to listen

24:23.592 --> 24:25.289
to any more of the dull things
that you have to say
for yourself.

24:25.464 --> 24:27.422
But I'm sorry about it.
I am, like.

24:29.946 --> 24:30.599
Are you dying?

24:31.339 --> 24:32.340
No, I'm not dying.

24:34.342 --> 24:36.083
But then you've loads of time.

24:36.257 --> 24:37.737
For chatting?

24:37.911 --> 24:40.000
Aye.For aimless chatting?

24:40.174 --> 24:42.785
Not for aimless chatting.
For good, normal chatting.

24:44.439 --> 24:46.963
So, we'll keep
aimlessly chatting

24:47.137 --> 24:49.313
and me life'll keep dwindling.

24:49.488 --> 24:53.317
And in 12 years,
I'll die with nothin'
to show for it

24:53.492 --> 24:56.407
bar the chats I've had
with a limited man,
is that it?

24:58.192 --> 25:01.369
I said,
"Not aimless chatting."

25:01.543 --> 25:04.981
I said,
"Good, normal chatting."

25:05.155 --> 25:08.115
The other night,
two hours you spent
talking to me

25:08.289 --> 25:10.552
about the things you found
in your little donkey's shite
that day.

25:10.726 --> 25:13.163
Two hours, Padraic.
I timed it.

25:13.337 --> 25:15.644
Well, it wasn't me
little donkey's shite, was it?

25:15.818 --> 25:18.342
It was me pony's shite,
which shows how much
you were listenin'.

25:18.517 --> 25:20.475
None of it helps me,
do you understand?

25:20.780 --> 25:22.956
None of it helps me.

25:31.704 --> 25:33.749
We'll just chat
about somethin' else then.

25:43.193 --> 25:44.194
[SIGHS]

25:58.600 --> 25:59.775
What's the matter with ya?

25:59.949 --> 26:01.168
Nothin'.

26:01.342 --> 26:02.517
Aren't we going for a sherry?

26:02.691 --> 26:03.692
Don't feel like it.

26:05.825 --> 26:08.697
No, I'm not having this
again today!

26:13.702 --> 26:15.878
Hey! What the hell's
going on with you
and me fecking brother?

26:16.183 --> 26:17.445
Don't come in here
shouting the odds at me

26:17.619 --> 26:18.664
in the middle
of the fecking day,
all right, Siobhan?

26:18.838 --> 26:20.317
You can't just all of a sudden

26:20.491 --> 26:21.841
stop being friends
with a fella!

26:22.015 --> 26:23.886
Why can't I?

26:24.191 --> 26:26.889
Why can't ya?
Because it isn't nice.

26:27.063 --> 26:27.977
Do you want a sherry, Siobhan?

26:28.151 --> 26:29.370
No!Righty-ho.

26:29.544 --> 26:30.676
Has he said somethin' to ya
when he was drunk?

26:30.850 --> 26:32.242
No, I prefer him
when he's drunk.

26:32.416 --> 26:34.201
It's all the rest of the time
I have the problem with.

26:34.375 --> 26:35.985
What's the fecking
matter, then?

26:36.159 --> 26:37.160
He's dull, Siobhan.

26:38.422 --> 26:39.119
He's what?

26:40.337 --> 26:41.338
He's dull.

26:44.385 --> 26:47.475
But he's always been dull.
What's changed?

26:48.607 --> 26:50.478
I've changed.

26:50.652 --> 26:53.786
I just don't have
a place for dullness
in me life anymore.

26:56.266 --> 26:58.617
But you live
on an island off the coast
of Ireland, Colm.

26:58.791 --> 27:01.532
What the hell
are you hoping for, like?

27:01.707 --> 27:03.360
For a bit of peace, Siobhan.
That's all.

27:05.188 --> 27:06.886
For a bit of peace
in me heart, like.

27:08.322 --> 27:11.107
You can understand that.
Can't ya?

27:20.421 --> 27:21.596
Can't ya?

27:25.600 --> 27:27.602
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

28:05.118 --> 28:07.163
Do you think I'm dull?

28:07.337 --> 28:10.210
No. 'Cause you're not dull,
you're nice.

28:10.384 --> 28:12.125
That's what I thought.
I mean, I'm a happy lad.

28:13.953 --> 28:15.302
Or I was.

28:15.476 --> 28:17.608
Till me best friend started
acting the gilly-gooly.

28:18.522 --> 28:19.959
It's him, Padraic.

28:21.177 --> 28:23.658
Maybe he's just depressed.

28:23.832 --> 28:26.748
[WHISPERS]
That's what I was thinking,
that he's depressed.

28:28.794 --> 28:29.795
[NORMALLY] Well, if he is,

28:29.969 --> 28:30.926
he could at least
keep it to himself, like.

28:31.100 --> 28:32.406
You know, push it down,
like the rest of us.

28:32.580 --> 28:33.886
[COWBELL JINGLES]

28:35.061 --> 28:36.932
No, Jenny!
[SNAPS FINGERS] Out!

28:37.106 --> 28:37.933
[COWBELL JINGLES]Out!

28:40.588 --> 28:42.111
She just wants
a bit of company, Siobhan.

28:42.285 --> 28:43.417
Animals is for outside,
I've told ya.

28:43.591 --> 28:44.592
[CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

28:48.944 --> 28:52.382
And people don't be laughing
at me behind me back,

28:52.556 --> 28:54.080
do they?

28:54.254 --> 28:55.472
No. Why would they be?

28:55.646 --> 28:57.605
They don't think
I'm dim or anything?

28:58.301 --> 28:59.302
Dim?

29:00.260 --> 29:00.956
No.

29:03.306 --> 29:04.481
You don't seem
very sure about it.

29:04.655 --> 29:05.918
Of course, I'm sure about it.

29:08.224 --> 29:10.009
Dominic's the dim one
on the island, isn't he?

29:11.227 --> 29:13.229
He is, aye. By miles.

29:15.231 --> 29:17.407
Uh, hang on, by miles.

29:17.581 --> 29:19.018
And then,
who's the next dimmest?

29:19.192 --> 29:20.497
Well, I don't like
to judge people

29:20.671 --> 29:21.847
in those terms now, do I?

29:22.021 --> 29:23.326
In what terms?In order of their dimness.

29:23.500 --> 29:25.111
Well, I know you don't.
And neither do I, do I?

29:25.285 --> 29:26.199
But try, like.No!

29:26.373 --> 29:27.853
I won't try.

29:28.027 --> 29:30.464
There's enough judgy people
on this fecking island, so no!

29:30.638 --> 29:32.248
You're not dim!

29:32.422 --> 29:34.381
You're a nice man, all right?
So, move on!

29:37.036 --> 29:38.167
I'm as clever as you, anyways.

29:38.341 --> 29:39.342
I know that at least.

29:39.516 --> 29:41.127
[UNDER BREATH] Yeah,
don't be fecking stupid.

29:41.562 --> 29:43.085
Huh?

29:43.259 --> 29:45.348
[BELL TOLLING][PEACEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

29:46.610 --> 29:48.003
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

30:20.079 --> 30:23.430
[PEACEFUL MUSIC
CONTINUES PLAYING]

30:29.566 --> 30:30.829
What happened to you?

30:31.003 --> 30:33.092
Me daddy discovered
the poteen situation.

30:33.266 --> 30:34.441
SIOBHAN: Oh, Jesus, Dominic!

30:34.615 --> 30:36.356
You poor thing, ya.

30:36.530 --> 30:38.140
What the hell
was he hittin' you with?

30:38.314 --> 30:39.620
A kettle was the final thing.

30:39.794 --> 30:41.013
I wouldn'ta minded,
but for the spout.

30:42.492 --> 30:43.493
Do you want a ride to church?

30:43.667 --> 30:44.799
Uh, feck them gobshites!

30:45.104 --> 30:46.322
Dominic!

30:46.496 --> 30:49.021
But could I stay the night
with ye the night?

30:49.195 --> 30:50.109
Just for the one night, like?

30:50.761 --> 30:52.546
SIOBHAN: Mm...

30:52.720 --> 30:55.244
Well, just
the one night, mind.

30:55.418 --> 30:57.812
Nice! I'll see ye
for supper, so.

30:58.117 --> 30:59.248
[CHUCKLES] Whoo-hoo!

31:07.778 --> 31:10.912
[PRAYING IN LATIN]

31:16.787 --> 31:18.485
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

31:34.153 --> 31:35.719
[WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

31:43.684 --> 31:45.164
Forgive me, Father,
for I have sinned.

31:45.338 --> 31:47.296
It's eight weeks
since my last confession,
I think.

31:48.428 --> 31:50.212
Go on, Colm.

31:50.517 --> 31:52.301
[SIGHS] Just the usual,
I suppose, Father.

31:52.475 --> 31:55.478
The drinking
and the impure thoughts.

31:55.652 --> 31:57.393
And a bit of pride, I suppose.

31:57.567 --> 32:00.266
Although I never really
saw that as a sin,
but sure I'm here now.

32:01.484 --> 32:02.181
And

32:03.660 --> 32:05.053
how's the despair?

32:06.533 --> 32:08.883
Not so much of it of late.
Thanks be.

32:11.842 --> 32:13.627
And why aren't you talking
to Padraic Suilleabhain
no more?

32:16.543 --> 32:18.719
That wouldn't be a sin, now,
would it, Father?

32:18.893 --> 32:22.201
It wouldn't be a sin, no,
but it's not very nice either,
is it?

32:23.898 --> 32:26.031
Who told you?

32:26.205 --> 32:28.729
It's an island, Colm.
Word gets around.

32:30.557 --> 32:33.255
Also, Padraic asked me
to put in a word, like.

32:34.256 --> 32:35.344
I see.

32:35.518 --> 32:36.258
So...

32:38.826 --> 32:40.393
It isn't him you have
the impure thoughts about,
is it?

32:41.785 --> 32:44.005
Are you joking me?

32:44.179 --> 32:46.921
I mean,
are you fecking joking me?

32:47.095 --> 32:50.620
People do have impure thoughts
about men, too.

32:50.794 --> 32:52.318
Do you have impure thoughts
about men, Father?

32:54.015 --> 32:56.800
I do not have
impure thoughts about men.

32:56.975 --> 32:59.934
And how dare you say that
about a man of the cloth?

33:00.108 --> 33:02.154
Well, you started it.

33:02.328 --> 33:04.852
Well, you can get out
of my confessional
right now, so you can.

33:05.026 --> 33:06.549
And I'm not forgiving you
any of these things

33:06.723 --> 33:08.551
until the next time,
so I'm not!

33:08.725 --> 33:09.944
Well, I better not be dying
in the meantime then,
eh, Father?

33:10.118 --> 33:10.814
I'll be pure fucked!

33:12.077 --> 33:13.252
You will be pure fucked!

33:13.426 --> 33:16.516
Yes, you will be pure fucked!

33:31.966 --> 33:33.272
Pint, Colm?

33:36.014 --> 33:37.667
If you don't
stop talkin' to me,

33:37.841 --> 33:39.669
and if you don't
stop botherin' me,

33:39.843 --> 33:41.671
or sendin' your sister
or your priest to bother me...

33:41.845 --> 33:43.238
I didn't send me sister
to bother you, did I?

33:43.412 --> 33:44.761
She has her own mind.

33:44.935 --> 33:46.676
Although, I did send
the priest though,
you have me there.

33:46.850 --> 33:49.114
What I've decided
to do is this.

33:49.288 --> 33:51.290
I have a set of shears
at home.

33:51.464 --> 33:54.293
And each time you bother me
from this day on,

33:54.467 --> 33:56.077
I'll take those shears

33:56.251 --> 33:57.644
and I'll take one
of me fingers off with them.

33:58.862 --> 34:00.386
And I'll give
that finger to ya.

34:00.560 --> 34:03.258
A finger from me left hand.
Me fiddle hand.

34:03.432 --> 34:05.478
And each day
you bother me more,

34:05.652 --> 34:07.001
another I'll take off
and I'll give ya

34:07.306 --> 34:09.656
until you see
sense enough to stop.

34:09.830 --> 34:12.702
Or until I have
no fingers left.

34:12.876 --> 34:14.443
Does this make things
clearer to ya?

34:15.923 --> 34:17.577
Not really, no.

34:17.751 --> 34:18.665
Because I don't want

34:18.839 --> 34:19.622
to hurt your
feelings, Padraic.

34:19.796 --> 34:20.841
I don't, like.

34:22.060 --> 34:23.017
But it feels like the drastic

34:23.191 --> 34:24.584
is the only option
left open to me.

34:24.758 --> 34:26.977
You've loads of options
left open to ya.

34:27.152 --> 34:28.936
How's fingers
the first port of call?

34:29.110 --> 34:33.071
Please, don't talk to me

34:33.375 --> 34:36.074
no more, Padraic. Please.

34:36.378 --> 34:37.814
I'm begging you.

34:37.988 --> 34:39.729
But...JONJO: Shush, like, Padraic.

34:39.903 --> 34:41.818
Just, you know, shush, like.Yeah, I'd shush, like.

34:41.992 --> 34:43.690
I will shush.

34:46.736 --> 34:48.695
Except me and me sister
were thinking

34:48.869 --> 34:51.654
[SOFTLY] you might just be
a bit depressed, Colm.

34:51.828 --> 34:55.397
And I tell you this much,
fingers just confirms it.

34:56.920 --> 34:59.184
Don't you think, Colm?

35:00.924 --> 35:02.622
Starting from now.

35:15.374 --> 35:16.244
[DOOR OPENS]

35:19.639 --> 35:21.206
[DOOR CLOSES]

35:21.380 --> 35:22.859
Well, I never heard the like.

35:23.033 --> 35:24.818
I never heard the like.
He must really not
like you, Padraic.

35:24.992 --> 35:26.559
Fingers!

35:26.733 --> 35:27.777
Jesus. He's serious, lads.

35:27.951 --> 35:29.388
JONJO: He is serious!

35:29.692 --> 35:31.041
You can see it
in his eyes he's serious.

35:31.216 --> 35:32.826
Just because
he thinks you're dull.

35:33.000 --> 35:34.175
That's going overboard!

35:34.349 --> 35:35.785
Who told you about the dull?

35:37.178 --> 35:38.484
Well, I overheard it.

35:38.658 --> 35:40.138
Like, what was I
supposed to do?

35:40.442 --> 35:42.009
I don't think you're dull.

35:42.183 --> 35:44.229
And jeez, if I was
to cut something off meself

35:44.403 --> 35:48.015
for every dull person
that came in here,
I'd only have me head left.

35:48.189 --> 35:49.059
Do you think I'm dull, Gerry?

35:49.408 --> 35:50.148
No.

35:51.888 --> 35:54.282
That said,

35:54.456 --> 35:57.329
I did think the two of ye
always made
a funny pairing, like.

35:57.503 --> 35:59.418
No, we didn't.JONJO: Yeah, ye did.

35:59.592 --> 36:01.159
Ye did. Obviously, ye did.

36:01.333 --> 36:04.031
'Cause now he'd rather
maim himself than talk to ya.

36:04.205 --> 36:05.859
Colm was always
more of a thinker.

36:06.033 --> 36:06.947
Huh?

36:07.121 --> 36:09.123
Why's every... I think.

36:09.297 --> 36:10.342
Ah, you don't, Padraic.

36:10.516 --> 36:12.257
You don't, Padraic.Your sister does.

36:12.431 --> 36:13.954
Your sister does, aye.
Siobhan does.You're more of a...

36:14.128 --> 36:15.347
You're more of a...
What is he?

36:15.521 --> 36:17.392
You're more one
of life's good guys.

36:17.566 --> 36:19.612
You're more one
of life's good guys, aye.

36:19.786 --> 36:20.917
Apart from when you're drunk.

36:21.091 --> 36:23.442
Apart from when
you're drunk, aye.

36:23.746 --> 36:26.096
I used to think
that'd be a nice thing to be.

36:26.271 --> 36:28.664
One of life's good guys.

36:28.838 --> 36:31.101
And now, it sounds like
the worst thing I ever heard.

36:31.276 --> 36:32.451
Ah, don't take it
like that, Padraic.

36:32.625 --> 36:34.366
Don't take it
like that, Padraic.

36:34.540 --> 36:35.628
We're on your side.

36:37.369 --> 36:39.066
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

36:49.859 --> 36:51.296
What are you smiling at?

36:58.216 --> 36:59.391
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

37:15.842 --> 37:18.801
What's this mope so mopey for?
He's just a fecking man, lads!

37:18.975 --> 37:20.194
A fat, ginger man!

37:21.108 --> 37:23.066
Ay yi yi.

37:23.241 --> 37:26.026
I'll tell ya this much.
Ye two are awful mopey hosts.

37:26.200 --> 37:28.202
Luckily, you won't have
to put up with us
more than one night, so,

37:28.507 --> 37:30.073
and try eatin'
with your mouth closed.

37:30.248 --> 37:31.553
Where are we now, France?

37:31.727 --> 37:33.033
Will you tell him, Padraic?

37:33.207 --> 37:35.470
Aye, stop being a little
fecking bollocks, Dominic.

37:35.644 --> 37:37.342
No. Just about
the mouth thing.

37:39.866 --> 37:42.260
Colm Doherty
and his fat fecking fingers.

37:42.434 --> 37:43.739
He probably
wouldn't even be able

37:43.913 --> 37:45.611
to cut through the blubber
on them fingers.

37:45.785 --> 37:47.090
Would you not want him
to have to do the one finger

37:47.265 --> 37:48.483
to see
if he was bluffing, like?

37:48.657 --> 37:49.658
No, we wouldn't.

37:49.832 --> 37:51.269
That's what I'd have him do,

37:51.443 --> 37:53.271
I'd have him do the one finger
to see if he was bluffin'.

37:53.445 --> 37:55.055
'Cause worst comes to worst,

37:55.229 --> 37:56.883
he can still play the fiddle
with four fingers,
I'll bet ya.

37:57.057 --> 37:58.276
Or the banjo.

37:58.580 --> 37:59.581
We don't want any of that.

37:59.755 --> 38:01.061
We just want nothing
to do with him no more.

38:01.235 --> 38:02.889
You don't. This gom does.

38:03.933 --> 38:05.283
I am a gom, is right.

38:05.457 --> 38:07.197
You're not a gom![DOMINIC SIGHS]

38:08.851 --> 38:10.331
DOMINIC: Jeez.

38:10.505 --> 38:12.290
This is a depressing house.

38:12.594 --> 38:14.640
Would you prefer your own, so?

38:14.814 --> 38:16.250
I've heard it's a barrel
of fecking laughs.

38:17.033 --> 38:18.731
Well, touche.

38:19.601 --> 38:20.950
Too what?

38:21.124 --> 38:23.126
Che. Touche.
It's from the French.

38:36.314 --> 38:38.316
And how is it, Siobhan,
that you was never married?

38:42.798 --> 38:44.017
It's none of your
fecking business

38:44.191 --> 38:45.932
how I was never
fecking married.

38:46.106 --> 38:46.889
How isn't it?

38:48.021 --> 38:48.978
How isn't it?

38:50.066 --> 38:50.850
Was you never wild?

38:52.112 --> 38:55.681
Wild? Was I never wild?

38:55.855 --> 38:57.509
I don't know what
you're talkin' about, Dominic.

38:57.683 --> 38:59.815
Wild, how? Angry?

38:59.989 --> 39:01.643
'Cause I'm gettin' angry now,
I can tell ya!

39:01.817 --> 39:03.210
Not angry. Wild.

39:03.384 --> 39:04.951
You just keep
sayin' wild, Dominic!

39:05.125 --> 39:06.561
Wild!My brother told you,
didn't he?

39:06.735 --> 39:07.823
That you'd be out in the road

39:07.997 --> 39:09.738
if you started
talking stupid to me?

39:09.912 --> 39:11.827
He said creepy, not stupid.

39:12.001 --> 39:12.959
Well, you've failed
on both counts, haven't ya?

39:13.133 --> 39:14.134
I have.

39:17.093 --> 39:18.791
I'm off to bed
and he's not stayin' here
another night, Padraic.

39:18.965 --> 39:20.532
I don't care
how depressed you are.

39:20.706 --> 39:22.142
I'd rather have the donkey in.

39:24.013 --> 39:24.710
[DOOR SHUTS]

39:27.669 --> 39:29.584
Foiled again.

39:29.758 --> 39:31.369
But "faint heart"
and all that.

39:40.116 --> 39:41.117
Here.

39:42.858 --> 39:45.295
Ye two, ye'll be all right.

39:47.341 --> 39:48.124
Will we be?

39:54.783 --> 39:56.481
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

40:05.751 --> 40:06.752
[CLICKING TONGUE]

40:38.261 --> 40:39.349
Hello there, Mrs. O'Riordan,
I've the milk outside for ya.

40:39.524 --> 40:41.134
So, it's the two weeks
you owe me for now, I think.

40:41.308 --> 40:43.005
Nobody has a lick of news

40:43.179 --> 40:45.355
for us from your side
of the island, Padraic.

40:45.530 --> 40:46.748
Are you going
to be the same as them?

40:46.922 --> 40:48.097
I am, Mrs. O'Riordan,
I'm afraid.

40:48.271 --> 40:50.012
And I'm in a bit
of a rush, so...

40:50.186 --> 40:53.189
Eileen Coughlan had no news.

40:53.363 --> 40:55.975
Vincent Shaughnessy
had no news.

40:56.149 --> 40:58.281
It was a poor old week
for news. But then it is,
sometimes.

40:58.456 --> 41:01.197
ColmSonnyLarry,
he had no news.

41:01.371 --> 41:02.851
Did he not?

41:03.025 --> 41:04.723
That man never talks.

41:04.897 --> 41:06.768
Eh, he talks sometimes.Up himself.

41:07.073 --> 41:09.249
Aye, aye, anyways, so,
it's the two weeks you owe me
for now, Mrs. O'Riordan.

41:09.423 --> 41:10.468
As I was sayin'.

41:10.772 --> 41:11.556
[REGISTER DINGS]

41:15.124 --> 41:16.343
Ladies.

41:16.517 --> 41:17.431
Oh, it's Peadar.

41:17.605 --> 41:19.999
Peadar always
has a rake of news.

41:20.173 --> 41:22.436
What news have you, Peadar?PEADAR: News, is it?

41:22.610 --> 41:25.178
Fella killed himself,
over Rosmuck way.

41:25.352 --> 41:27.093
Walked into a lake
for himself.

41:27.267 --> 41:29.704
Twenty-nine and nothing wrong
with him, the fool.

41:29.878 --> 41:31.358
God love us!

41:31.532 --> 41:33.491
PEADAR: No,
not "God love us." Fool!

41:33.795 --> 41:34.796
Another fella,

41:34.970 --> 41:36.406
Protestant, of course,

41:36.581 --> 41:38.670
stabbed his missus
in Letterkenny.

41:38.844 --> 41:40.585
Six times he stabbed her.

41:40.759 --> 41:43.022
Good God!
And did she die, Peadar?

41:43.196 --> 41:44.806
She did die, aye.

41:45.111 --> 41:46.721
It wasn't with a spoon
he was stabbin' her.

41:46.895 --> 41:48.331
That's a lot of news.

41:48.506 --> 41:51.857
This man has no news,
don't ya not? No-Newsy!

41:52.031 --> 41:53.293
[PEADAR LAUGHS]

41:53.467 --> 41:55.164
Stukes never have news.MRS. O'RIORDAN: Stukes!

41:55.338 --> 41:56.775
[LAUGHS] Funny.

41:57.079 --> 41:59.821
There was a bit of news
I remembered, Mrs. O'Riordan.

41:59.995 --> 42:01.997
Dominic Kearney's father
beat Dominic senseless

42:02.171 --> 42:03.390
with a kettle Saturday,

42:03.564 --> 42:05.348
and is staying with me
and me sister, Dominic is.

42:05.523 --> 42:07.002
So, at least his father'll
take a bit of a break

42:07.176 --> 42:07.873
from his beatin' of him.

42:09.091 --> 42:10.919
And him, a policeman.

42:11.093 --> 42:13.052
Isn't that news?

42:13.226 --> 42:15.489
Ar, that Dominic's
an awful little bollocks.

42:15.794 --> 42:16.882
That's no news.

42:17.056 --> 42:19.319
Still, he was in a bad way
when I came upon him.

42:19.493 --> 42:21.539
I'd beat him
with a kettle meself
if I wasn't old.

42:21.713 --> 42:23.976
It's news is all I'm sayin'.

42:24.150 --> 42:26.326
That's no news.
That's shite news.

42:26.500 --> 42:27.980
Okay, so, Mrs. O'Riordan,
thanks for the...

42:29.068 --> 42:30.373
I'll see ya when I see ya.

42:33.942 --> 42:34.639
[DOOR THUDS, BELL RINGS]

42:37.729 --> 42:39.426
[BIRDS SQUAWK IN DISTANCE]

42:49.392 --> 42:50.393
[THUDS]

42:52.570 --> 42:54.093
And you can tell
that skitter of a son of mine

42:54.267 --> 42:56.051
he'd better be home
by teatime,

42:56.225 --> 42:57.923
or it's over to batter
the both of ye I'll be,

42:58.097 --> 42:59.446
and your dreary
fecking sister, too!

43:03.232 --> 43:04.233
[GROANS]

43:10.326 --> 43:11.719
Oh, hello there, Colm.

43:11.893 --> 43:14.243
Will I see you
at Jonjo's tonight
for that pint you owe me?

43:14.417 --> 43:15.418
I owe you no pin...

43:16.594 --> 43:17.290
You will, Peadar.

43:17.464 --> 43:18.770
Good man yourself.

43:25.515 --> 43:27.517
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

44:06.339 --> 44:08.167
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

44:22.355 --> 44:23.486
[SOBBING]

44:30.624 --> 44:31.843
Whoa, stand.

44:32.582 --> 44:33.583
Stand.

44:59.087 --> 45:00.306
[MELODIOUS FIDDLE
MUSIC PLAYING]

45:39.171 --> 45:39.867
[EXHALES]

45:43.697 --> 45:44.654
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

46:08.504 --> 46:10.202
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

46:12.682 --> 46:13.727
[WHISPERING]
What's that, Jenny?

46:16.382 --> 46:17.513
Will we go to the pub
for ourselves?

46:19.559 --> 46:20.778
We will. Come on.

46:38.491 --> 46:40.580
One drink you're havin', lady,
then it's off home with ya.

46:40.754 --> 46:43.017
I've a shirt that
wants ironing for the morning.

46:44.497 --> 46:46.412
Okay, Daddy.

46:46.586 --> 46:50.068
Aye. Off to the mainland
in the morning I'm headin'.

46:50.372 --> 46:51.721
That's why I need
the clean shirt, like.

46:53.898 --> 46:56.117
"And why are you off
to the mainland
in the mornin', Peadar?"

46:56.422 --> 46:58.859
Oh, thanks for asking, Colm.
I'll tell ya why.

46:59.033 --> 47:00.382
They've asked
for extra manpower

47:00.556 --> 47:02.384
for a couple of the
[WHISPERS] executions

47:02.558 --> 47:04.734
[NORMALLY] in case there's
any kind of a to-do, like.

47:04.909 --> 47:07.215
Six bob and a free lunch
they're payin' me.

47:07.389 --> 47:09.652
And sure I'd have gone
for nothin'.

47:09.827 --> 47:12.220
I've always wanted
to see an execution,
haven't you?

47:12.394 --> 47:14.135
Although, I'd have
preferred a hanging.

47:14.309 --> 47:15.963
Who are they executin'?

47:16.137 --> 47:18.705
The Free State lads
are executin' a couple
of the IRA lads.

47:20.533 --> 47:21.795
Or is it the other way around?

47:22.622 --> 47:23.536
[SCOFFS]

47:23.710 --> 47:26.669
I find it hard
to follow these days.

47:26.844 --> 47:28.541
Wasn't it so much easier
when we was all
on the same side,

47:28.715 --> 47:30.673
and it was just the English
we was killin'?

47:30.848 --> 47:33.502
I think it was.
I preferred it.

47:33.676 --> 47:35.591
But you don't care
who's executin' who?

47:35.765 --> 47:38.159
For six bob and a free lunch,
I don't care!

47:38.464 --> 47:39.769
They could be
executin' you. [CHUCKLES]

47:41.075 --> 47:42.511
Why don't you come with me?

47:42.685 --> 47:44.774
You could write
a miserable feckin' song
about it.

47:47.952 --> 47:49.518
Nah, I'm only messin'.

47:49.692 --> 47:51.607
[MUFFLED FOLK MUSIC PLAYING]

48:14.761 --> 48:16.197
Who are them?

48:16.502 --> 48:18.286
Music students, I think,
from Lisdoonvarna.

48:21.289 --> 48:22.203
[TALKING INDISTINCTLY]

48:30.646 --> 48:33.432
Another whisky,
anyways, Jonjo.

48:33.606 --> 48:36.174
Jeez, you're goin' at it
at a fair old lick
tonight, Padraic.

48:36.348 --> 48:38.306
Yeah? What's it to ya?

48:39.351 --> 48:40.700
[DRUM INTRO PLAYS]

48:45.270 --> 48:47.141
[PLAYING TRADITIONAL
MARCH MUSIC]

49:09.555 --> 49:10.643
Padraic, don't now...

49:14.734 --> 49:15.865
Go get Siobhan,
Dominic, would ya?

49:17.998 --> 49:20.218
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

49:20.522 --> 49:21.871
PEADAR: What are you
after, gobshite?

49:22.046 --> 49:23.699
Another beatin', is it?

49:23.873 --> 49:25.832
You, copper, I'm allowed
to chat to you, aren't I?

49:26.006 --> 49:27.965
It's just tubbyguts
I'm not allowed to talk to.

49:28.139 --> 49:29.749
Actually, no, I'd rather
you didn't talk to me neither.

49:30.880 --> 49:33.013
Oh, well, anyways,

49:33.187 --> 49:35.276
do you want to know
what the three things
that I hate the most

49:35.450 --> 49:36.364
on Inisherin is?Not really.

49:36.799 --> 49:37.887
One,

49:38.845 --> 49:39.846
policemen.

49:40.803 --> 49:42.370
Two,

49:42.544 --> 49:43.241
pudgy fiddle players.

49:44.851 --> 49:46.809
And three... [VOICE CRACKS]

49:46.984 --> 49:49.073
Wait, I had some funny thing
for three. What was it?

49:49.247 --> 49:51.684
Uh, I'll start again. One, um,

49:51.858 --> 49:53.164
policemen.

49:53.338 --> 49:54.295
Two...

49:55.949 --> 49:57.298
Pudgy fiddle players.

49:57.472 --> 49:59.561
PADRAIC: Pudgy fiddle players.

49:59.735 --> 50:01.476
And shite, what was three?

50:01.650 --> 50:03.217
Go on back
to your own gang now, Padraic.
I'm serious, now.

50:03.391 --> 50:04.175
[SHOUTING] Serious, are ya?

50:05.828 --> 50:06.786
[MUSIC HALTS]

50:06.960 --> 50:09.049
And talkin' to me, are ya?

50:11.443 --> 50:12.183
DOMINIC: Siobhan!

50:15.273 --> 50:17.318
Padraic's out of his brains
on whisky, and Colm's there.

50:17.492 --> 50:18.624
You'd better come.

50:25.979 --> 50:28.547
You, Colm Doherty,
do you know
what you used to be?

50:28.721 --> 50:30.549
No, Padraic,
what did I used to be?

50:30.723 --> 50:31.506
Nice!

50:32.551 --> 50:33.856
You used to be nice!

50:34.727 --> 50:36.511
Didn't he not?

50:36.685 --> 50:38.470
And now,
do you know what you are?

50:38.948 --> 50:40.211
Not nice.

50:40.385 --> 50:42.561
Ah, well,

50:42.735 --> 50:46.086
I suppose niceness
doesn't last then,
does it, Padraic?

50:46.260 --> 50:47.914
But will I tell ya something
that does last?

50:48.088 --> 50:50.656
What? And don't say
somethin' stupid like music.

50:50.830 --> 50:52.832
Music lasts.Knew it!

50:53.006 --> 50:55.791
And paintings last.
And poetry lasts.

50:55.965 --> 50:57.532
So does niceness.[DOOR OPENS]

51:00.883 --> 51:02.015
COLM: Do you know
who we remember

51:02.189 --> 51:04.322
for how nice they was
in the 17th century?

51:04.496 --> 51:06.715
PADRAIC: Who?Absolutely no one.

51:06.889 --> 51:09.849
Yet we all remember
the music of the time.

51:10.023 --> 51:11.981
Everyone, to a man,
knows Mozart's name.

51:12.156 --> 51:13.983
Well, I don't,
so there goes that theory.

51:15.768 --> 51:17.639
And anyway,
we're talkin' about niceness.

51:18.466 --> 51:19.554
Not whatsisname.

51:21.034 --> 51:22.992
My mammy, she was nice.

51:23.906 --> 51:26.561
I remember her.

51:26.735 --> 51:28.781
And my daddy, he was nice.
I remember him.

51:28.955 --> 51:31.653
And my sister, she's nice.

51:31.827 --> 51:35.092
I'll remember her.
Forever I'll remember her.

51:35.266 --> 51:37.529
COLM: And who else will?PADRAIC: "Who else will" what?

51:37.703 --> 51:39.748
Remember Siobhan
and your niceness?

51:40.923 --> 51:41.620
No one will.

51:42.534 --> 51:43.535
In 50 years' time,

51:43.709 --> 51:45.580
no one will remember
any of us.

51:47.974 --> 51:50.455
Yet the music of a man
who lived two centuries ago...

51:50.629 --> 51:52.370
"Yet," he says,
like he's English.

51:53.806 --> 51:54.937
Come home, Padraic.

51:55.112 --> 51:58.115
I don't give a feck
about Mozart,

51:58.724 --> 52:00.378
or Borvoven,

52:00.552 --> 52:03.685
or any of them
funny name feckers.

52:03.859 --> 52:05.296
I'm Padraic Suilleabhain.

52:07.689 --> 52:09.474
And I'm nice.

52:09.648 --> 52:11.171
SIOBHAN: [WHISPERS] Come home.

52:11.345 --> 52:13.565
So you'd rather be friends
with this fella, would ya?

52:14.087 --> 52:15.741
A fella who

52:15.915 --> 52:17.395
beats his own son
black and blue every night

52:17.699 --> 52:18.135
that he's not fiddling
with him.

52:20.093 --> 52:22.574
I never told him that, Daddy.
He's... He's just drunk now.

52:23.531 --> 52:24.924
You used to be nice.

52:26.621 --> 52:27.970
Or did you never used to be?

52:30.799 --> 52:32.018
Oh, God.

52:35.195 --> 52:36.936
Maybe you never used to be.

52:50.906 --> 52:52.038
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

52:53.735 --> 52:55.433
I'll have a word
with him, Colm.

52:55.737 --> 52:57.609
You don't need
to do anything drastic.

52:57.783 --> 52:59.437
He won't be
botherin' you no more.

52:59.611 --> 53:00.612
That's a shame.

53:02.179 --> 53:03.789
That's the most interesting
he's ever been.

53:03.963 --> 53:04.964
I think I like him again now.

53:05.138 --> 53:06.313
[MAN CHUCKLES]

53:08.968 --> 53:12.493
It was the 18th century,
anyway. Mozart.

53:13.146 --> 53:14.365
Not the 17th.

53:19.935 --> 53:22.590
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

53:23.461 --> 53:25.419
[RAIN PATTERING]

53:25.593 --> 53:27.291
[GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

53:32.948 --> 53:33.732
[SIGHS]

53:50.444 --> 53:53.230
Siobhan Suilleabhain!
Well, well.

53:53.404 --> 53:55.144
I only came in for rashers,
Mrs. O'Riordan.

53:55.319 --> 53:56.450
I've no time to talk,
I'm afraid.

53:56.624 --> 53:57.712
Letter came for ya.

54:01.238 --> 54:02.717
Fell open, did it?

54:02.891 --> 54:03.979
Aye, in the heat, I suppose.

54:05.590 --> 54:06.286
[SIGHS]

54:10.899 --> 54:11.900
A job offer, is it?

54:19.038 --> 54:23.129
A job offer from a library
on the mainland, is it?

54:23.303 --> 54:26.567
Just the rashers,
please, Mrs. O'Riordan.
About ten of them.

54:35.010 --> 54:36.708
You never tell me anything!

54:39.493 --> 54:40.929
Well, it'd crucify him,
your leaving!

54:41.103 --> 54:42.627
Hey, no one's leaving!

54:57.990 --> 54:59.818
Listen, I didn't
come down to chat.

54:59.992 --> 55:01.298
I just came down to say
that all that last night

55:01.602 --> 55:02.995
was just
the whisky talkin', Colm.

55:03.169 --> 55:04.170
All what last night?

55:04.344 --> 55:06.303
All whatever it was
I was sayin'.

55:06.477 --> 55:07.304
What were you sayin'?

55:07.608 --> 55:10.568
Uh... Yeah.
I can't remember much of it,

55:10.872 --> 55:13.048
but I remember the gist
of it wasn't the best.

55:13.222 --> 55:14.659
You always know, don't ya?

55:18.358 --> 55:21.100
Well, anyways, I just wanted
to say I was sorry.

55:21.274 --> 55:22.057
Will we leave it at that?

55:24.190 --> 55:25.713
Why can't you just
leave me alone, Padraic?

55:27.193 --> 55:28.760
PADRAIC: Huh?

55:28.934 --> 55:30.631
I've already told ya,
haven't I?

55:30.805 --> 55:32.241
Yeah, I know. I was just...

55:32.416 --> 55:34.113
I mean, why can't you
just leave me alone?

55:46.821 --> 55:48.170
What are ya doing?I don't know.

55:49.607 --> 55:51.043
For fuck's sake, like.

55:59.921 --> 56:00.835
How... How's the new tune?

56:02.097 --> 56:02.794
What?

56:13.935 --> 56:15.937
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

56:17.286 --> 56:19.637
Ar, for God's sake, Padraic.

56:19.811 --> 56:21.116
How many more times?

56:21.290 --> 56:24.685
I am not putting
me donkey outside
when I am sad, okay?

56:24.990 --> 56:26.383
Well, stringy bits of shite
I had to pick up

56:26.687 --> 56:27.993
yesterday when ya let her in!

56:28.167 --> 56:30.038
There was no stringy bits
in that donkey's shite.

56:30.212 --> 56:32.084
There was bits of straw,
if there was anything.

56:32.258 --> 56:33.999
Maybe it was straw, so.

56:36.044 --> 56:38.090
[SIGHS] I'll get us
our porridge.

56:57.718 --> 56:58.458
Was I awful last night?

57:02.114 --> 57:04.290
No, you was lovely.

57:04.464 --> 57:06.640
Well, I know I wasn't lovely
now, Siobhan. [CHUCKLES]

57:06.814 --> 57:09.251
You were lovely.
About me, anyways.

57:09.426 --> 57:12.429
Of course
I was lovely about you.

57:12.603 --> 57:13.952
What else is there
to be about ya?

57:14.126 --> 57:14.866
[SIOBHAN CHUCKLES]

57:15.040 --> 57:16.041
[DOOR THUDS]

57:27.356 --> 57:29.358
[SOFT SUSPENSEFUL
MUSIC PLAYING]

58:20.148 --> 58:21.149
What was that? A bird?

58:22.411 --> 58:23.804
What was what?

58:23.978 --> 58:24.805
The bang at the door.

58:25.414 --> 58:26.459
A bird?

58:26.807 --> 58:27.504
Aye.No.

58:29.201 --> 58:30.507
What was it, so?

58:30.681 --> 58:32.204
The bang at the door?Aye!

58:32.378 --> 58:33.466
What was the bang
at the door?[SCOFFS]

58:33.771 --> 58:35.512
It was, uh...

58:35.816 --> 58:36.817
hard to lie...

58:36.991 --> 58:39.298
it was, uh...

58:39.472 --> 58:41.822
[HESITATES] a finger.

58:43.128 --> 58:44.042
[CHUCKLES]

58:45.826 --> 58:46.784
A what?

58:47.306 --> 58:48.002
Finger.

58:48.829 --> 58:50.309
[SHRIEKS]

58:50.483 --> 58:51.702
Jesus, Siobhan!
You'll frighten
the little fella!

58:51.876 --> 58:53.442
Throw it out, Padraic!

58:53.617 --> 58:55.270
I'm not throwing
his finger out!
It'll get dirt on it!

58:55.444 --> 58:56.620
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

58:59.274 --> 59:00.014
Where... Where'd you put it?

59:02.277 --> 59:03.540
Shoebox.

59:03.844 --> 59:05.846
Oh, my. Oh, God.

59:06.020 --> 59:06.717
Well,

59:08.283 --> 59:09.197
he's serious, then.

59:26.606 --> 59:28.565
[PLAYING MELODIOUS TUNE]

1:00:26.623 --> 1:00:28.320
Do we have to have it in here
while we're eating?

1:00:28.494 --> 1:00:30.235
Once I finish me porridge,
I'll bring it back to him.

1:00:30.409 --> 1:00:32.541
[SCOFFS]

1:00:32.716 --> 1:00:35.719
[CHUCKLES IN DISBELIEF]
Are you feckin' stupid?

1:00:35.893 --> 1:00:39.113
I mean,
are you feckin' stupid?

1:00:39.287 --> 1:00:41.289
No, I'm not feckin' stupid.
We've had this discussion.

1:00:41.463 --> 1:00:43.727
You've got to leave him
alone now, Padraic. For good!

1:00:45.076 --> 1:00:45.990
Do you think?

1:00:46.164 --> 1:00:48.470
Do I think? Yeah, I do think!

1:00:48.645 --> 1:00:51.299
He's cut his
feckin' finger off,
and thrown it at ya!

1:00:51.473 --> 1:00:53.171
Come on! It wasn't at me.

1:00:55.652 --> 1:00:57.566
Well, what are we going to do?

1:00:57.741 --> 1:00:59.481
We can't keep a man's finger.

1:01:07.402 --> 1:01:08.403
[DOOR SHUTS]

1:01:16.716 --> 1:01:18.152
[RIFLE FIRING IN DISTANCE]

1:01:25.986 --> 1:01:27.596
Jesus, Colm!

1:01:29.120 --> 1:01:30.904
Did it hurt?

1:01:31.078 --> 1:01:33.385
[SCOFFS]
Hurt awful to begin with.
Thought I was going to faint.

1:01:35.387 --> 1:01:38.651
It's funny, feels fine now,
in all the excitement.

1:01:41.088 --> 1:01:42.437
Would you like a cup of tea?

1:01:42.611 --> 1:01:45.223
I won't, Colm. I only came up
to give you your finger back.

1:01:46.137 --> 1:01:47.007
Oh, yeah?

1:01:48.530 --> 1:01:49.618
Thanks.

1:01:51.490 --> 1:01:53.666
Cleared up
quite nice, actually.

1:01:53.840 --> 1:01:56.190
And you wouldn't
have thought it would.

1:01:56.364 --> 1:01:58.410
What do you need
from him, Colm?

1:01:58.584 --> 1:02:00.020
To end all this?

1:02:03.632 --> 1:02:04.764
Silence, Siobhan.

1:02:05.547 --> 1:02:08.115
Just silence.

1:02:08.289 --> 1:02:12.685
One more silent man
on Inisherin, good-oh!

1:02:12.990 --> 1:02:14.208
Silence it is, so.

1:02:16.689 --> 1:02:19.083
This isn't about Inisherin.

1:02:19.257 --> 1:02:20.171
It's about one boring man

1:02:20.345 --> 1:02:22.129
leaving another man alone,
that's all.

1:02:22.303 --> 1:02:26.264
"One boring man"!
You're all fecking boring!

1:02:26.438 --> 1:02:28.788
With your piddling grievances
over nothin'!

1:02:28.962 --> 1:02:31.486
You're all fecking boring!

1:02:32.879 --> 1:02:35.142
I'll see he doesn't talk
to you no more.

1:02:35.316 --> 1:02:37.405
Do.

1:02:37.579 --> 1:02:40.278
Else it'll be all four of them
the next time,
not just the one.

1:02:41.714 --> 1:02:42.846
You're not serious.

1:02:45.587 --> 1:02:47.589
Well, that won't help
your fecking music.

1:02:48.373 --> 1:02:50.114
Aye.

1:02:50.288 --> 1:02:51.506
We're gettin' somewhere now.

1:02:54.509 --> 1:02:58.078
[CHUCKLES] I think
you might be ill, Colm.

1:02:58.252 --> 1:02:59.297
[CHUCKLES LIGHTLY]

1:02:59.471 --> 1:03:02.822
Do worry sometimes
I'm just entertaining meself

1:03:02.996 --> 1:03:04.606
while I stave off
the inevitable.

1:03:06.521 --> 1:03:07.696
Don't you?

1:03:10.264 --> 1:03:11.744
No, I don't.

1:03:14.703 --> 1:03:15.661
Yeah, you do.

1:03:36.421 --> 1:03:38.118
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

1:04:25.818 --> 1:04:27.864
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

1:04:52.584 --> 1:04:53.672
COLM: Declan!

1:04:59.678 --> 1:05:01.375
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION]

1:05:19.872 --> 1:05:21.569
[DECLAN LAUGHING]

1:05:24.094 --> 1:05:25.791
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATION
CONTINUES]

1:05:40.893 --> 1:05:41.938
Howdo!

1:05:42.808 --> 1:05:43.896
Howdo!

1:05:44.201 --> 1:05:45.071
Do you want a ride?

1:05:46.725 --> 1:05:48.205
I will so.

1:05:48.379 --> 1:05:49.293
Thanks, fella!

1:05:52.731 --> 1:05:53.427
[CLICKS TONGUE]

1:05:59.085 --> 1:06:01.609
Oh, no, you're not
that student fella
from Lisdoonvarna, are ya?

1:06:01.783 --> 1:06:03.220
I am. I'm Declan.

1:06:03.872 --> 1:06:05.787
Why?

1:06:05.962 --> 1:06:06.963
They told me
at the post office
to try to find

1:06:07.137 --> 1:06:09.313
that student fella, Declan,
from Lisdoonvarna.

1:06:09.487 --> 1:06:10.923
Yeah, a telegram came for ya.

1:06:11.228 --> 1:06:12.925
From your mammy.

1:06:13.099 --> 1:06:14.753
My mammy is no longer with us.

1:06:14.927 --> 1:06:16.885
Not your mammy, sorry.
[FALTERS]

1:06:17.060 --> 1:06:18.757
Did I say your mammy?
Your auntie.
Yeah, your auntie.

1:06:18.931 --> 1:06:20.541
It's about your daddy.

1:06:20.715 --> 1:06:22.195
What about Daddy?

1:06:22.369 --> 1:06:24.937
Uh, bread van
crashed into him.

1:06:25.242 --> 1:06:27.113
The bread van?Yeah.

1:06:27.287 --> 1:06:29.072
They said you'd best
hurry home to him,
lest he should die all alone.

1:06:29.768 --> 1:06:30.987
Die?

1:06:31.161 --> 1:06:33.337
Or get worse, all alone.

1:06:35.730 --> 1:06:36.688
This is impossible.

1:06:36.862 --> 1:06:38.603
It's not impossible.

1:06:38.777 --> 1:06:40.387
Bread vans crash
into people all the time.

1:06:40.561 --> 1:06:41.258
I know!

1:06:42.346 --> 1:06:43.695
That's how me mammy died.

1:06:46.872 --> 1:06:48.874
[JUMPS OFF]

1:06:49.048 --> 1:06:51.572
If it's the same fecking
bread van, I'll kill them.

1:06:59.841 --> 1:07:00.668
[TUGS REINS]

1:07:08.459 --> 1:07:09.155
Thanks.

1:07:11.766 --> 1:07:13.681
What were you talking
to the boat fella for?

1:07:13.855 --> 1:07:16.293
For none of your fecking
business, I think it was.

1:07:16.597 --> 1:07:18.338
Of course, it's me business.
Aren't I the law?

1:07:18.512 --> 1:07:19.600
[SOFTLY] Fecking knob.

1:07:20.384 --> 1:07:21.428
Huh?

1:07:21.602 --> 1:07:23.082
Well, you can tell
that whiny brother of yours

1:07:23.256 --> 1:07:25.432
I'll be around soon
for that battering I owe him.

1:07:25.606 --> 1:07:27.086
A battering?

1:07:27.260 --> 1:07:29.436
That'd be good, actually.
It might take him
out of himself.

1:07:29.610 --> 1:07:31.264
Huh?

1:07:31.438 --> 1:07:33.484
You're an awful strange lady.

1:07:34.311 --> 1:07:35.529
No wonder no one likes ya.

1:07:37.792 --> 1:07:38.706
[PEADAR CHUCKLES]

1:07:54.809 --> 1:07:56.289
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

1:07:59.640 --> 1:08:00.815
[FOOTSTEPS FADE]

1:08:04.036 --> 1:08:05.298
[GASPS] Oh.

1:08:05.472 --> 1:08:06.995
Hello there, Mrs. McCormick.

1:08:07.170 --> 1:08:11.348
A death shall
come to Inisherin
afore the month is out.

1:08:11.913 --> 1:08:13.437
A death, huh?

1:08:13.611 --> 1:08:15.961
Maybe even two deaths.

1:08:17.049 --> 1:08:18.050
Well, that'd be sad.

1:08:19.965 --> 1:08:22.054
We shall pray to the Lord

1:08:22.228 --> 1:08:26.537
'tis neither you,
nor poor Siobhan,
will be either of them.

1:08:26.711 --> 1:08:28.626
Well, is that a nice thing
to be sayin'?

1:08:28.800 --> 1:08:30.628
I wasn't trying to be nice.

1:08:31.890 --> 1:08:33.892
I was trying to be accurate.

1:08:34.849 --> 1:08:35.981
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDING]

1:08:38.375 --> 1:08:39.637
[SOFTLY] Fecking hell.

1:08:47.558 --> 1:08:50.126
[SORROWFUL CLASSICAL
MUSIC PLAYING]

1:09:03.530 --> 1:09:05.228
[SIOBHAN CRYING SOFTLY]

1:09:12.409 --> 1:09:13.845
What's the matter?

1:09:15.847 --> 1:09:16.935
Nothing.

1:09:17.936 --> 1:09:18.850
[SNIFFLES]

1:09:19.024 --> 1:09:20.721
[SIOBHAN BREATHING SHAKILY]

1:09:29.252 --> 1:09:31.950
[SORROWFUL CLASSICAL MUSIC
CONTINUES PLAYING]

1:09:43.353 --> 1:09:44.658
[DOMINIC SIGHS, MUMBLES]

1:09:51.796 --> 1:09:53.189
Me daddy say
he's gonna kill you Sunday

1:09:53.363 --> 1:09:55.060
for spilling the beans
about that fiddling with me.

1:09:56.061 --> 1:09:57.193
[SCOFFS]

1:10:00.065 --> 1:10:01.806
"Kill me," kill me,
or, you know,

1:10:01.980 --> 1:10:04.461
"beat me up a bit," kill me?

1:10:04.635 --> 1:10:07.115
"Beat you up a bit," kill ya,
I think.

1:10:07.290 --> 1:10:08.900
Although he did
kill a man once.

1:10:13.426 --> 1:10:15.559
I'm sorry for that spilling
the beans on ya, Dominic.

1:10:16.473 --> 1:10:18.518
I was out of order that night.

1:10:18.823 --> 1:10:21.217
You was funny
apart from that bit.

1:10:21.391 --> 1:10:24.437
That's why I don't understand
why that fat fella
threw the finger at ya.

1:10:24.611 --> 1:10:25.830
He seemed fine
when you were slagging him.

1:10:26.004 --> 1:10:27.788
He did not.

1:10:27.962 --> 1:10:29.486
Did he?

1:10:29.790 --> 1:10:32.358
"That's the most interesting
Padraic's ever been," he said.

1:10:34.055 --> 1:10:35.013
"I think I like him
again now."

1:10:40.845 --> 1:10:41.715
Aye.

1:10:44.196 --> 1:10:47.547
Maybe this whole thing
has just been about
gettin' you to try a new tack,

1:10:47.721 --> 1:10:49.201
start standin' up
for yourself a bit.

1:10:50.202 --> 1:10:51.508
Do you think?

1:10:51.682 --> 1:10:53.988
Yeah, and be less of a,
you know,

1:10:54.162 --> 1:10:55.251
whiny little dull-arse.

1:10:57.818 --> 1:10:59.559
Well, I have been less
of a whiny little
dull-arse, actually.

1:10:59.733 --> 1:11:00.952
Have ya, yeah?

1:11:01.126 --> 1:11:02.954
Just yesterday,
there was this musician fella

1:11:03.128 --> 1:11:04.869
that Colm was
getting along great with.

1:11:05.043 --> 1:11:06.044
And what did I do?

1:11:06.218 --> 1:11:07.219
I went and sent him
packing from the island.

1:11:07.959 --> 1:11:09.743
Did ya? How?

1:11:09.917 --> 1:11:11.832
I told him a bread van
crashed into his daddy,

1:11:12.006 --> 1:11:13.791
and he'd have to be rushing
home to him, lest he die.

1:11:17.838 --> 1:11:18.839
Oh...

1:11:22.278 --> 1:11:23.888
That sounds like
the meanest thing
I've ever heard.

1:11:25.106 --> 1:11:27.195
Huh?

1:11:27.370 --> 1:11:30.764
Well, aye,
it was a bit mean, but...

1:11:32.549 --> 1:11:34.202
he'll be fine
once he gets home

1:11:34.377 --> 1:11:35.421
and he finds his daddy
hasn't been hit
by a bread van.

1:11:38.903 --> 1:11:40.731
I used to think
you were the nicest of them.

1:11:42.907 --> 1:11:44.082
Turns out you're just
the same as them.

1:11:44.256 --> 1:11:45.866
I am the nicest of them.

1:11:49.130 --> 1:11:49.957
Ar, Dominic, now!

1:11:53.047 --> 1:11:55.049
Well, maybe I'm not
a happy lad, so!

1:11:57.182 --> 1:11:58.705
Maybe this is the new me!

1:12:00.968 --> 1:12:01.969
Aye.

1:12:03.536 --> 1:12:05.059
Maybe this is the new me.

1:12:10.108 --> 1:12:12.023
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING]

1:12:39.833 --> 1:12:40.834
DOMINIC: Howdo![GASPS]

1:12:41.008 --> 1:12:42.749
Jesus Christ, Dominic!

1:12:42.923 --> 1:12:44.925
Would you ever stop
creeping up on people?

1:12:45.099 --> 1:12:46.927
You almost gave me
a fecking heart attack!

1:12:47.101 --> 1:12:48.102
I wasn't creeping up on ya.

1:12:48.276 --> 1:12:49.277
I was sidling up on ya.

1:12:49.452 --> 1:12:51.454
Between you
and that ghoul, Jesus!

1:12:51.628 --> 1:12:54.326
I always call her
a ghoul, too,
because she is a ghoul.

1:12:54.500 --> 1:12:56.981
Jeez, we have a lot
in common, don't we?
Me and you.

1:12:57.155 --> 1:12:59.113
Calling old people
ghouls and that.

1:13:02.987 --> 1:13:04.858
[SIGHS] It's a great old lake,
isn't it?

1:13:10.081 --> 1:13:12.126
I'm glad
I caught you, actually.

1:13:12.300 --> 1:13:14.955
Because there
was somethin' I was wantin'
to ask ya, actually.

1:13:15.129 --> 1:13:18.002
And discovering how much
we have in common,

1:13:18.176 --> 1:13:20.831
well, it just makes me
want to ask you even more.

1:13:21.005 --> 1:13:22.136
We don't have
anything in common.

1:13:22.310 --> 1:13:24.704
Uh, don't skip ahead.

1:13:24.878 --> 1:13:26.880
But yeah, what I was wantin'
to ask you was...

1:13:29.274 --> 1:13:31.276
Somethin' along
the lines of...

1:13:31.450 --> 1:13:33.800
Should've planned
this, really.

1:13:33.974 --> 1:13:35.672
Well, yeah, what I was wantin'
to ask you was...

1:13:41.199 --> 1:13:43.419
You probably wouldn't
ever want to, I don't know,

1:13:44.898 --> 1:13:46.726
to fall in love with a boy
like me, would ya?

1:13:49.947 --> 1:13:52.689
Oh, Dominic,
I don't think so, love.

1:13:52.863 --> 1:13:55.518
No, yeah, no.
Uh, I was thinking no.

1:13:58.695 --> 1:14:01.175
Not even in the future, like?
Like when I'm your age?

1:14:08.966 --> 1:14:12.360
Yeah, no, I didn't think so.

1:14:12.535 --> 1:14:14.928
Just thought I'd ask
on the off chance, you know,

1:14:15.102 --> 1:14:16.756
like, "faint heart" and that.[BOTH CHUCKLE]

1:14:22.762 --> 1:14:24.285
Well, there goes that dream.

1:14:30.727 --> 1:14:32.511
Well,

1:14:32.685 --> 1:14:35.862
I best go over there
and do whatever that thing
over there I was gonna do was.

1:14:37.211 --> 1:14:38.038
Mm-hmm.

1:14:55.142 --> 1:14:58.015
♪♪ I walked from Mallow Town

1:14:58.189 --> 1:15:01.366
♪♪ To Aghadoe, Aghadoe

1:15:01.540 --> 1:15:05.065
♪♪ I took his head
from the jail gate to Aghadoe

1:15:05.239 --> 1:15:06.458
Come on, Sammy,
you have to dance too.

1:15:09.200 --> 1:15:12.203
♪♪ Like an Irish king he sleeps
in Aghadoe ♪♪

1:15:12.377 --> 1:15:13.378
[DOOR SLAMS OPEN]

1:15:14.422 --> 1:15:15.772
How are you, fatty?

1:15:15.946 --> 1:15:17.208
Dancing with your dog, is it?

1:15:17.382 --> 1:15:18.470
Well, who else
is gonna dance with ya?

1:15:18.644 --> 1:15:20.254
Your poor dog
has no say in the matter.

1:15:20.428 --> 1:15:22.387
And if you're too rude
to be offering me a seat,

1:15:22.561 --> 1:15:24.389
I'll be taking
one of me own accord!

1:15:26.478 --> 1:15:28.828
Now, how's that
for an old hello?

1:15:29.002 --> 1:15:30.874
Have you gone fecking mental?

1:15:31.048 --> 1:15:32.919
Have I gone fecking mental?

1:15:33.093 --> 1:15:36.444
No, I haven't gone
fecking mental, actually.

1:15:36.619 --> 1:15:38.534
Not only have I not gone
fecking mental,

1:15:38.708 --> 1:15:41.493
but I have ten fingers
to prove I've not gone
fecking mental.

1:15:41.667 --> 1:15:43.277
How many fingers do you have
to prove you've not gone
fecking mental?

1:15:43.451 --> 1:15:45.062
Nine fingers.

1:15:45.236 --> 1:15:47.107
And nine fingers
is the epitome of mental.

1:15:48.892 --> 1:15:51.459
That's right. The epitome!

1:15:51.634 --> 1:15:54.462
Heh. There'll be none of that!
I didn't come here for licks!

1:15:54.637 --> 1:15:55.638
I came here
for the opposite of licks.

1:15:55.812 --> 1:15:56.508
What's the opposite of licks?

1:15:56.856 --> 1:15:57.596
Huh?

1:15:58.945 --> 1:16:00.207
What did you come here for?

1:16:00.381 --> 1:16:03.123
I didn't come here
for anythin', did I?

1:16:03.297 --> 1:16:04.734
I just came
to kick your door in
and give you a slagging.

1:16:04.908 --> 1:16:06.431
Well, you've done that,
so you can go now.

1:16:06.605 --> 1:16:08.259
Haven't finished yet, have I?

1:16:08.433 --> 1:16:10.174
Well, I finished
with your door.

1:16:10.348 --> 1:16:12.089
I haven't finished
with your slagging.

1:16:12.263 --> 1:16:14.395
We were doin'
so well, Padraic.

1:16:14.570 --> 1:16:16.093
I wasn't doing so well.

1:16:18.617 --> 1:16:20.619
I was doing terrible.

1:16:20.793 --> 1:16:22.621
All right,
I was doin' so well.

1:16:22.795 --> 1:16:24.754
Yeah, well, it can't all be
you, you, you, can it?

1:16:24.928 --> 1:16:26.494
Yes, it can.

1:16:26.669 --> 1:16:28.453
There's two of us in this.No, there isn't.

1:16:28.627 --> 1:16:29.846
It takes two to tango.

1:16:30.020 --> 1:16:31.543
I don't want to tango.

1:16:31.717 --> 1:16:33.545
Well, you danced
with your dog.

1:16:34.415 --> 1:16:35.242
[CLICKS TONGUE]

1:16:45.775 --> 1:16:48.952
Talkin' of tangos,
how's your new tune
comin' along?

1:16:49.126 --> 1:16:51.084
[SIGHS] I just
finished it, actually.

1:16:51.998 --> 1:16:52.651
Just this morning.

1:16:54.261 --> 1:16:56.002
No, Colm, that's great, like!

1:16:56.176 --> 1:16:58.135
That's why I was dancing
with me dog.

1:16:59.440 --> 1:17:01.355
I don't usually dance
with me dog.

1:17:01.529 --> 1:17:04.402
[CHUCKLES] There's no harm
dancin' with your dog.

1:17:04.576 --> 1:17:07.405
I'd dance with me donkey
if I knew how. And she did.

1:17:09.973 --> 1:17:11.191
Is it good?

1:17:11.365 --> 1:17:12.279
Your tune?

1:17:16.588 --> 1:17:19.330
Mm, what's it called?

1:17:19.504 --> 1:17:22.072
"The Banshees of Inisherin,"
I was thinking.

1:17:24.857 --> 1:17:27.294
But there are no banshees
on Inisherin.

1:17:27.468 --> 1:17:29.383
I know, I just like
the double S-H sounds.

1:17:31.168 --> 1:17:32.735
Aye.

1:17:32.909 --> 1:17:35.302
There's plenty
of double S-H on Inisherin.

1:17:35.476 --> 1:17:36.390
Yeah.

1:17:36.564 --> 1:17:39.742
Maybe there are banshees, too.

1:17:39.916 --> 1:17:43.615
I just don't think
that they scream
to portend death anymore.

1:17:43.789 --> 1:17:48.098
I think they just
sit back, amused, and observe.

1:17:49.142 --> 1:17:50.056
Portend?

1:17:51.144 --> 1:17:52.145
Yeah.

1:17:55.714 --> 1:17:58.195
I keep having thoughts
about playing it for you
at your funeral.

1:17:58.369 --> 1:18:00.545
But that wouldn't be fair
on either of us, would it?

1:18:09.554 --> 1:18:10.381
[GULPS]

1:18:14.472 --> 1:18:17.518
Well, that's great that you
finished your tune, Colm.

1:18:17.693 --> 1:18:18.781
That's more than great.

1:18:19.956 --> 1:18:20.696
That's...

1:18:22.349 --> 1:18:23.307
really great.

1:18:31.402 --> 1:18:32.403
[COLM SIGHS]

1:18:34.927 --> 1:18:37.930
[SIGHS] So, do you want
to meet me down the pub, Colm?

1:18:39.279 --> 1:18:41.020
We could celebrate
your tune, like.

1:18:41.194 --> 1:18:45.329
[CLOCK CHIMES TWICE]

1:18:47.940 --> 1:18:50.116
Only if you'd like, like.

1:18:50.290 --> 1:18:53.032
But I could run up ahead.
Order them in.

1:18:56.470 --> 1:18:57.820
Why don't you
do that, Padraic?

1:19:00.300 --> 1:19:01.432
Why don't I run up...

1:19:03.782 --> 1:19:04.652
and order them?

1:19:06.742 --> 1:19:07.568
Well, I will so.

1:19:11.311 --> 1:19:13.487
Jeez, that went well!
And maybe on the way,

1:19:13.661 --> 1:19:15.707
I can find that student friend
of yours, that Declan fella!

1:19:15.881 --> 1:19:17.491
I told him
his daddy was dying,
so he'd feck off home

1:19:17.665 --> 1:19:20.233
and leave us alone,
but there's no need now!

1:19:20.407 --> 1:19:21.626
Sure he could join us.

1:20:01.971 --> 1:20:02.841
[PADRAIC CLEARS THROAT]

1:20:11.284 --> 1:20:12.372
[EXHALES, SNIFFS]

1:20:14.853 --> 1:20:16.812
What are you sitting
over there for
when I'm over here?

1:20:16.986 --> 1:20:18.901
Just thought I'd have a sit
for meself, you know.

1:20:20.337 --> 1:20:21.642
Wait for me friend.

1:20:21.817 --> 1:20:23.775
Are you fecking joking me?

1:20:23.949 --> 1:20:25.472
Your four-fingered friend?

1:20:25.646 --> 1:20:26.909
I mean,
are you fecking joking me?

1:20:27.083 --> 1:20:29.302
No, I'm not fecking joking ya.

1:20:29.476 --> 1:20:31.261
He just needed
a bit of tough love was all.

1:20:33.393 --> 1:20:34.568
[BARKING]

1:20:47.494 --> 1:20:52.978
[CLOCK CHIMES FOUR TIMES]

1:20:54.675 --> 1:20:55.720
[JONJO SIGHS]

1:20:57.722 --> 1:20:59.245
[FOOTSTEPS OUTSIDE]

1:21:06.165 --> 1:21:07.645
Siobhan, do you want a sherry?

1:21:07.819 --> 1:21:09.038
No.Righty-ho.

1:21:11.301 --> 1:21:12.302
What are you doin'?

1:21:12.476 --> 1:21:13.607
Me?Yes, you.

1:21:13.781 --> 1:21:15.566
Nothing. Just drinkin'.

1:21:15.740 --> 1:21:17.568
Not waitin'?Not waitin'.

1:21:17.742 --> 1:21:19.135
Well, he is waitin', Siobhan.
He's waitin' for Colm Doherty.

1:21:19.309 --> 1:21:20.223
I amn't waitin'.

1:21:20.397 --> 1:21:21.354
He just told me
he was waitin'.

1:21:21.528 --> 1:21:22.921
Telltale!

1:21:26.011 --> 1:21:30.189
Come home with me, Padraic.
I've somethin' to discuss
with ya.

1:21:30.494 --> 1:21:31.625
You've somethin'
to discuss with me?

1:21:33.192 --> 1:21:34.933
That sounds, uh...

1:21:35.107 --> 1:21:37.196
I don't want
to discuss somethin'.

1:21:37.501 --> 1:21:39.895
Well, ya have to,
'cause I'm leavin'.

1:21:41.548 --> 1:21:42.375
Leavin'?

1:21:45.726 --> 1:21:46.684
Like leavin'?

1:21:48.773 --> 1:21:49.469
Like...

1:21:51.558 --> 1:21:52.298
not staying?

1:21:56.824 --> 1:21:57.825
Yeah.

1:22:10.012 --> 1:22:11.709
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

1:22:18.237 --> 1:22:19.021
[DOOR THUDS]

1:22:27.638 --> 1:22:28.639
[DOOR THUDS]

1:22:30.249 --> 1:22:32.121
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

1:22:41.782 --> 1:22:42.914
But what about me?

1:22:43.219 --> 1:22:44.437
What about you?

1:22:44.611 --> 1:22:45.873
I'll have no friends
at all left!

1:22:46.048 --> 1:22:48.137
You'll have Dominic.Ah here!

1:22:48.311 --> 1:22:50.530
And he's gone off me now, too.

1:22:50.704 --> 1:22:52.358
What kind of a place is it
when the village gom
goes off ya?

1:22:53.577 --> 1:22:55.492
And who's gonna
do the cookin'?

1:22:55.666 --> 1:22:57.798
Oh, that's your
first question, isn't it?
"Who's gonna do the cookin'?"

1:22:57.973 --> 1:22:59.583
Well, it wasn't me
first question, was it?

1:22:59.757 --> 1:23:01.237
"But what about me?"
was me first question.

1:23:05.241 --> 1:23:07.112
[SOMBER MUSIC CONTINUES]

1:23:35.271 --> 1:23:36.620
[SIOBHAN GASPING]

1:23:36.794 --> 1:23:37.708
Padraic.

1:23:39.623 --> 1:23:40.754
Padraic!

1:23:44.758 --> 1:23:47.718
PADRAIC: Now?
But you can't be leavin' now!

1:23:47.892 --> 1:23:49.937
I can be leavin' now.
[SNIFFLES]

1:23:50.112 --> 1:23:52.505
I can't be waitin' round
for any more of this madness!

1:23:52.679 --> 1:23:54.899
What the hell
did you say to him, Padraic?

1:23:55.073 --> 1:23:56.031
Nothin' really.

1:23:56.335 --> 1:23:57.554
[SCOFFS]

1:23:57.728 --> 1:23:59.686
Well, I'd sort of had a chat
with Dominic earlier.

1:23:59.860 --> 1:24:00.818
[FALTERS]

1:24:00.992 --> 1:24:03.168
And a new sort of,

1:24:03.342 --> 1:24:06.258
you know, standin' up
for meself sort of tack
we thought I should try.

1:24:06.432 --> 1:24:07.825
God!

1:24:07.999 --> 1:24:10.088
It was all going fine
until he chopped off
all his fingers.

1:24:12.873 --> 1:24:14.962
[SNIFFLING, BREATH SHUDDERING]

1:24:19.184 --> 1:24:20.881
Me books wouldn't fit.

1:24:22.318 --> 1:24:24.407
Would you look
after them for me?

1:24:24.581 --> 1:24:26.278
Ar, don't go, Siobhan.

1:24:26.452 --> 1:24:28.019
They're all I have, really.

1:24:30.239 --> 1:24:31.849
Apart from the obvious.

1:24:32.023 --> 1:24:32.763
[BREATH SHUDDERS]

1:24:37.811 --> 1:24:39.552
[CRIES]

1:24:39.726 --> 1:24:41.728
You'll be back soon,
won't you, Siobhan?

1:24:42.816 --> 1:24:45.297
[CRIES] Oh, Padraic!

1:24:45.471 --> 1:24:46.994
Don't say, "Oh, Padraic."

1:24:47.908 --> 1:24:49.388
Say yes.

1:25:00.007 --> 1:25:01.879
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING]

1:25:19.897 --> 1:25:21.116
[SEAGULLS CALLING]

1:25:22.204 --> 1:25:23.509
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1:25:38.959 --> 1:25:41.005
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC CONTINUES]

1:26:19.609 --> 1:26:20.392
[MUSIC FADES]

1:27:05.089 --> 1:27:06.786
[SOFT SUSPENSEFUL
MUSIC PLAYING]

1:27:47.174 --> 1:27:48.915
[EXHALES HEAVILY]

1:27:58.838 --> 1:27:59.752
[SNIFFLES]

1:28:04.148 --> 1:28:05.236
[SMACKS LIPS]

1:28:06.759 --> 1:28:07.804
Ah, Jenny.

1:28:09.893 --> 1:28:11.024
[SNIFFLING]

1:28:18.815 --> 1:28:19.903
[BREATHES SHAKILY]

1:28:27.954 --> 1:28:28.955
[SHUDDERS]

1:28:38.617 --> 1:28:39.444
[SIGHS]

1:28:43.056 --> 1:28:44.493
[SNIFFLING]

1:28:48.061 --> 1:28:48.758
Oh.

1:28:53.023 --> 1:28:55.199
[MELANCHOLY OPERATIC
MUSIC PLAYING]

1:30:17.803 --> 1:30:18.500
[SIGHS]

1:30:53.273 --> 1:30:54.623
I don't want to talk.

1:30:55.798 --> 1:30:57.626
Don't go killin' his dog now.

1:30:57.800 --> 1:30:58.844
And don't be puttin' things
in me head

1:30:59.018 --> 1:31:00.106
that weren't there
in the first feckin' place,

1:31:00.280 --> 1:31:01.456
you feckin' nutbag!

1:31:02.761 --> 1:31:04.197
[CHUCKLING] "Nutbag!"

1:31:06.591 --> 1:31:08.288
[BROODING MUSIC PLAYING]

1:31:57.729 --> 1:31:59.209
What would I ever
hurt you for?

1:32:01.341 --> 1:32:02.952
You're the only nice thing
about him.

1:32:09.698 --> 1:32:11.613
[LIVELY FOLK MUSIC PLAYING]

1:32:13.440 --> 1:32:15.268
[SCATTING ALONG TO MUSIC]

1:32:26.062 --> 1:32:26.758
[COLM LAUGHS]

1:32:33.330 --> 1:32:34.984
How are you, Padraic?
You're lookin' well.

1:32:43.253 --> 1:32:44.167
That's lovely, lads.

1:32:49.564 --> 1:32:51.174
I don't need your apologies,
all right?

1:32:52.131 --> 1:32:53.829
It's a relief to me.

1:32:54.003 --> 1:32:55.570
So, let's just call it quits

1:32:55.744 --> 1:32:58.137
and agree to go
our separate ways,
for good this time.

1:33:01.401 --> 1:33:04.143
Your fat fingers
killed me little donkey today.

1:33:04.317 --> 1:33:07.190
So, no, we won't
call it quits.

1:33:07.364 --> 1:33:08.060
We'll call it the start.

1:33:09.584 --> 1:33:11.020
You're jokin' me.Yeah, no.

1:33:11.194 --> 1:33:12.978
I'm not jokin' ya.

1:33:13.152 --> 1:33:14.980
So tomorrow, Sunday,

1:33:15.154 --> 1:33:17.548
God's day, around 2:00,

1:33:17.722 --> 1:33:19.811
I'm going to call up
to your house
and I'm gonna set fire to it,

1:33:19.985 --> 1:33:21.770
and hopefully
you'll still be inside it.

1:33:23.249 --> 1:33:24.773
But I won't be checkin'
either way.

1:33:27.993 --> 1:33:29.473
Just be sure
and leave your dog outside.

1:33:31.040 --> 1:33:32.694
I've nothing against that gom.

1:33:35.261 --> 1:33:37.786
Or you can do whatever's
in your power to stop me.

1:33:41.528 --> 1:33:43.269
To our graves
we're taking this.

1:33:45.228 --> 1:33:46.621
To one of our graves, anyways.

1:33:48.971 --> 1:33:50.189
PEADAR: Here.

1:33:50.363 --> 1:33:52.322
I've a bone to pick
with you, dreary.

1:33:52.496 --> 1:33:54.150
Is that little gobshite
of mine at your place again?

1:33:54.324 --> 1:33:55.978
Leave him, Peadar.
His donkey's just died.

1:33:56.500 --> 1:33:57.893
Did he?

1:33:58.067 --> 1:33:59.590
The little miniature fella?

1:33:59.764 --> 1:34:01.810
Well, Jesus, boys,
I'll tell ya this much...

1:34:14.300 --> 1:34:15.127
Two o'clock.

1:34:21.264 --> 1:34:22.221
[DOOR CLOSES]

1:34:27.313 --> 1:34:29.141
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING][BELL TOLLING]

1:34:43.939 --> 1:34:45.636
[PRIEST PRAYING IN LATIN]

1:35:11.618 --> 1:35:12.707
[PARTITION SLIDES]

1:35:15.753 --> 1:35:16.885
[CLICKS TONGUE SOFTLY]

1:35:17.059 --> 1:35:18.495
I killed a miniature donkey.

1:35:22.629 --> 1:35:24.196
It was by accident...

1:35:27.765 --> 1:35:29.027
but I do feel bad about it.

1:35:32.291 --> 1:35:35.860
Do you think God gives a damn
about miniature donkeys, Colm?

1:35:38.210 --> 1:35:39.211
I fear he doesn't.

1:35:42.475 --> 1:35:44.608
And I fear that's where
it's all gone wrong.

1:35:47.437 --> 1:35:48.177
Is that it?

1:35:49.526 --> 1:35:51.484
Is what it?

1:35:51.658 --> 1:35:53.008
Aren't you forgetting
a couple of things?

1:35:54.923 --> 1:35:57.664
No, I think I've covered it.

1:35:57.839 --> 1:36:00.929
[SIGHS] Wouldn't you say
punching a policeman is a sin?

1:36:02.278 --> 1:36:03.975
Ah here.

1:36:04.149 --> 1:36:06.108
If punching a policeman
is a sin,

1:36:06.282 --> 1:36:08.980
we may as well just
pack up and go home.

1:36:10.939 --> 1:36:12.897
And self-mutilation is a sin.

1:36:14.159 --> 1:36:15.160
It's one of the biggest.

1:36:16.292 --> 1:36:17.597
Is it?

1:36:17.772 --> 1:36:20.644
Self-mutilation,
so you have me there.

1:36:20.818 --> 1:36:21.993
Multiplied by five.

1:36:27.738 --> 1:36:29.261
How's the despair?

1:36:34.136 --> 1:36:35.180
It's back a bit.

1:36:38.444 --> 1:36:40.142
But you're not gonna
do anything about it?

1:36:44.711 --> 1:36:46.801
I'm not gonna
do anything about it, no.

1:36:54.417 --> 1:36:56.114
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

1:37:01.728 --> 1:37:03.905
SIOBHAN: Dear Padraic,

1:37:04.079 --> 1:37:08.126
I am safely ensconced
in the mainland and, Padraic,
it's lovely here.

1:37:08.431 --> 1:37:10.781
There's a river running
past my window as I write,

1:37:10.955 --> 1:37:13.915
and the people already seem
less bitter and mental.

1:37:14.089 --> 1:37:18.354
I'm not sure why, but I think
it's 'cause a lot of them
are from Spain.

1:37:18.528 --> 1:37:22.053
Mostly, I wanted to say
there's a spare bed here
for you, Padraic.

1:37:22.227 --> 1:37:25.796
And with the war almost over,
I think there'd be work
for ya here.

1:37:25.970 --> 1:37:28.407
Because there's nothing
for you on Inisherin.

1:37:28.581 --> 1:37:30.932
Nothing but more
bleakness and grudges

1:37:31.106 --> 1:37:33.760
and loneliness and spite

1:37:33.935 --> 1:37:36.763
and the slow passing of time
until death.

1:37:36.938 --> 1:37:38.417
And sure,
you can do that anywhere.

1:37:41.638 --> 1:37:44.771
So come, Padraic. Leave there.

1:37:44.946 --> 1:37:47.644
Dominic can look after Jenny
and the rest of your animals.

1:37:47.818 --> 1:37:49.820
They could move
into the house together.

1:37:49.994 --> 1:37:51.953
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

1:37:59.656 --> 1:38:00.352
Hut!

1:38:22.505 --> 1:38:25.160
SIOBHAN: So come now,
Padraic, please.

1:38:29.164 --> 1:38:31.122
Before it's all too late.

1:38:50.881 --> 1:38:52.883
[SENTIMENTAL OPERATIC
MUSIC PLAYING]

1:39:50.245 --> 1:39:53.204
[CLOCK CHIMES TWICE][PANTING]

1:40:18.099 --> 1:40:19.796
[MELANCHOLY MUSIC PLAYING]

1:40:57.138 --> 1:40:58.008
[COWBELL JINGLES]

1:41:09.759 --> 1:41:10.499
[SCRATCHING ON DOOR]

1:41:12.109 --> 1:41:12.805
[SNAPS FINGERS]

1:41:22.250 --> 1:41:23.947
PADRAIC: Dear Siobhan.

1:41:24.121 --> 1:41:27.342
Obviously, I don't know
what "ensconced" is,

1:41:27.516 --> 1:41:30.693
but I thank you for the offer
of the free bed
and the whatnot.

1:41:30.867 --> 1:41:32.912
But I won't be takin' you up
on it, I'm afraid.

1:41:34.740 --> 1:41:37.265
As I told you,
me life is on Inisherin.

1:41:37.439 --> 1:41:39.093
Me friends, me animals.

1:41:43.227 --> 1:41:44.707
Even now as I write,

1:41:44.881 --> 1:41:46.752
little donkey Jenny
is looking at me, saying,

1:41:46.926 --> 1:41:49.364
"Please don't go, Padraic.
We'd miss ya."

1:41:49.668 --> 1:41:51.714
And nuzzling me,
the gilly-gooly.

1:41:52.802 --> 1:41:53.890
Get off, Jenny.

1:41:57.633 --> 1:41:58.329
MRS. McCORMICK: Psst!

1:42:08.600 --> 1:42:10.080
PADRAIC: In other news,

1:42:10.385 --> 1:42:12.909
in sadder news, actually,

1:42:13.083 --> 1:42:15.259
I won't be able to ask Dominic
anything, I'm afraid.

1:42:18.132 --> 1:42:20.003
Because they found him
in the lake this morning.

1:42:24.877 --> 1:42:27.315
I suppose he must've slipped
and fell in.

1:42:36.150 --> 1:42:38.326
So, there'd be
no one to take care
of the animals, anyway.

1:42:54.690 --> 1:42:56.605
[GLASS SMASHING]

1:43:02.045 --> 1:43:03.568
No other news, really.

1:43:13.056 --> 1:43:14.797
Except that
I love you, Siobhan.

1:43:15.972 --> 1:43:17.147
And I miss ya.

1:43:19.932 --> 1:43:21.847
And I hope I'll see ya
again someday.

1:43:24.850 --> 1:43:26.200
If you ever come back home.

1:43:29.159 --> 1:43:31.248
Come back home, Siobhan.

1:43:36.645 --> 1:43:39.256
Yours sincerely,
your loving brother...

1:43:41.693 --> 1:43:42.955
Padraic Suilleabhain.

1:43:54.140 --> 1:43:56.099
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

1:44:32.178 --> 1:44:33.267
[BARKS]

1:44:56.246 --> 1:44:59.380
[WAVES CRASHING]

1:45:17.311 --> 1:45:19.008
Suppose me house
makes us quits.

1:45:21.227 --> 1:45:24.187
If you'd stayed in your house,
that would've made us quits.

1:45:24.361 --> 1:45:26.494
But you didn't, did ya,
so it doesn't, does it?

1:45:38.593 --> 1:45:40.638
I'm sorry
about your donkey, Padraic.

1:45:41.335 --> 1:45:42.423
Honestly, I am.

1:45:45.339 --> 1:45:46.818
I don't fucking care.

1:46:03.313 --> 1:46:06.272
Haven't heard any rifle fire
from the mainland
in a day or two.

1:46:06.447 --> 1:46:09.145
I think they're coming
to the end of it.

1:46:09.319 --> 1:46:12.148
I'm sure they'll be
at it again soon enough,
aren't you?

1:46:14.368 --> 1:46:16.195
Some things
there's no movin' on from.

1:46:19.677 --> 1:46:21.157
And I think
that's a good thing.

1:46:44.049 --> 1:46:44.920
Padraic.

1:46:51.361 --> 1:46:53.624
Thanks for lookin'
after me dog
for me, anyways.

1:47:00.109 --> 1:47:00.979
Any time.

1:47:16.952 --> 1:47:18.649
[SCATTING]

1:47:35.449 --> 1:47:37.842
[SENTIMENTAL OPERATIC
MUSIC PLAYING]

1:49:26.516 --> 1:49:28.213
[INSTRUMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]
